summary: An Ordinance providing for the improvement of West Hinds Street, in the City of Seattle, from California Avenue to Fifty-first Avenue Southwest, by grading and curbing the same, and by constructing the necessary drainage, in accordance with Resolution No. 1371 of the City Council of the City of Seattle, and providing for the payment therefor by the mode of "Payment by Bonds," as provided by the laws of the State of Washington and the Charter and Ordinances of the City of Seattle
